# Line-ending policy. Some files here are CRYPTOGRAPHICALLY SIGNIFICANT: the
# external-verification suite_digest is SHA-256 over the RAW BYTES of each
# conformance vector file. A Windows clone with the default core.autocrlf=true
# rewrites those files to CRLF on checkout, silently breaking the digest for any
# external verifier (this bit a real implementer twice). Pin them to verbatim
# bytes so every clone, on every OS, reproduces our published digests.
conformance/vectors/** -text
examples/external-verification/statements/** -text

# Everything else: normalize to LF in the repo and on checkout.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries: never touch.
*.pdf binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.mp4 binary
*.woff2 binary
